track_notes: This track includes activating Eagle Hill, then going on to Eagle Mountain Ridge for a second activation, returning the same way.  This double activation will end up with just over 1,000 meters elevation gain because you will have to regain Eagle Hill on your return.  You can park at the closed gate and bike up the logging road which is being maintained for biking by the David Thompson area Forestry Dept.  You can bike right to the summit of Eagle Hill and stash your bike at the summit.  You can then hike down the back of Eagle Hill and gain Eagle Mountain Ridge via a good trail that only become indistinct in a few places where it departs from the maintained bike trail.  On your return, you have to climb back to the summit of Eagle Hill to fetch your bike for the exhilarating ride down the logging road to your car.
